<title>USA: Selfcare Q1 shr loss $0.74 vs loss $2.61.</title>
<headline>Selfcare Q1 shr loss $0.74 vs loss $2.61.</headline>
<dateline>WALTHAM, Mass. 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three Months Ended March 31,</p>
<p>				     1997	     1996</p>
<p>Net revenues		 $ 9,094,607    $ 2,469,401</p>
<p>Operating loss		(3,816,651)    (8,158,385)</p>
<p>Net loss			(4,894,115)   (16,316,324)</p>
<p>Net loss per common and</p>
<p> common equivalent share	 (0.74)	  $(2.61)</p>
<p>Weighted average number of common</p>
<p>and common equivalent shares</p>
<p> outstanding		    6,591,261	6,247,515</p>
<p>NOTE: The first quarter 1997 results included an unrealized loss on foreign currency translation of $719,000 which, if excluded, would have resulted in a net loss of approximately $4.2 million or ($0.63) per common and common equivalent share.  The first quarter of 1996 included a non-cash compensation charge of $5.6 million and a non-cash interest expense of $8.1 million which, if excluded, would have resulted in a net loss of approximately $2.6 million or $0.42 per common and common equivalent share.</p>
<p>Full company name is Selfcare Inc.</p>
<p>--((New York Newsdesk 212-859-1610))</p>
